Product description

Three-way Master Dimmer Switches

How to connect it to WiFi？

  • Make sure your network is 2.4G (NOT 5G)
  • Open Smartlife/Treatlife APP and log in
  • Power on your switch, press and hold the on/off button for 5 seconds until the red indicator light blinks rapidly, then hold the button again for 5 seconds until it blinks slowly
  • Follow in-app instruction and link to 2.4G hotspot

Three-way master dimmer switches allow you to replace a current three-way setup in a hallway and use the other master switch in a bedroom.

Control 1% to 100% brightness of 1 light from 2 places just by sliding your fingers up and down, control them even when you aren’t home. Dimmers give you the wonderful feature of dimming the lights from your phone.

  • Specifications:
  • Rated Voltage: 120V/60HZ
  • Max Power: 150W LED, 150W CFL, 400W INC
  • Wireless Standard: IEEE 802.11 b/g/n, 2.4GHz
  • Applicable Equipment: Non-intelligent dimmable light bulbs


APP Remote Control

With the Treatlife APP, you can use your phone anywhere to check that lights are turned off when you are away and turn them off remotely if anyone accidentally leaves them on.


Schedule and Timer

Set a schedule using the APP to change the brightness or turn on or off. It's nice to have a timer that will make the lights on when you get home at night.


Group Control

You can add a group of Treatlife smart dimmer switch in the APP and turn on all lights in the house with one click, share the device to your family members.

Q1: The switch isn’t functioning properly. What should I do?

If the switch isn’t working after installation, please check all wires are securely connected and that the wire caps are tightly fastened. Loose connections can prevent the switch from receiving power, causing malfunctions. Confirm that the neutral wire is properly connected. For detailed troubleshooting steps, refer to the user manual or contact our support team for assistance.

Q2: How do I properly install and use the 3-Way smart dimmer switch?

A: The 3-Way Smart Dimmer Switch can function as either a 3-way switch or a single-pole main switch. If you install it in a 3-way, identify and replace only one of the two existing 3-way switches. The other switch must remain a standard (non-smart) 3-way switch—do not use two smart switches in the same circuit. Install the smart switch on the power source side, where the power source enters the circuit. Wiring it on the wrong side will cause it to malfunction.

Q3: The switch makes the light flicker. What could be the issue?

A: Ensure you are using non-smart dimmable bulbs. The switch supports dimmable LED (max 150W), halogen/incandescent (max 400W), and CFL (max 150W) bulbs. Non-dimmable bulbs may fail to adjust brightness properly and light with remote or smart light may lead to flicker.

Q4: The switch won’t connect to Wi-Fi. What should I check?

A: Ensure that your Wi-Fi is set to 2.4GHz, as the switch does not support 5GHz networks. Also, place the router closer to the switch for a stronger signal. If the issue persists, restart your router and try resetting the switch.

Q5: The switch is not connecting to Alexa or is unresponsive. What should I do?

A: First, make sure the switch is successfully connected and is online in the app before linking it to Alexa. Then, check that the correct Alexa skill is enabled and the device is properly linked in the Alexa app. If the switch is still unresponsive, try re-discovering devices in Alexa, restart both the switch and Echo device, and ensure your 2.4G Wi-Fi connection is stable.

      I recently upgraded my home with TreatLife's 3-way smart switches, and the results have been nothing short of amazing. These switches have truly elevated my smart home setup, and I couldn't be happier with the overall experience.

      Ease of Installation: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

      These three-way switches look and work great, are affordable, and are simple to install in a modern standard sized switchbox. I also really like their combination fan and light controllers for rooms with ceiling fans which eliminate the need for seperate switches and therefore can actually save space in the switchbox.
      I'll be buying more of these to complete my smart home project.
